import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='population', y='engineers', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between population and number of engineers in each state?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='hurricanes', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of hurricanes in each state?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Number of Hurricanes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.axvline(data['hurricanes'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Hurricanes: {:.2f}'.format(data['hurricanes'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    high_hurricane_states = data[data['hurricanes'] > 50]
    high_hurricane_states = high_hurricane_states.sort_values(by='population', ascending=False)
    ax = sns.barplot(x="state", y="population", data=high_hurricane_states, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.axhline(y=high_hurricane_states['population'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Population')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha="right")
    ax.set_xlabel('States with high number of hurricanes')
    ax.set_ylabel('Population')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='engineers', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['engineers'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['engineers'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of engineers in each state?')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Engineers')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
